<HEADLINE> American Yacht Leads in Whitbread </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- American yacht Toshiba gains
ground on overall leader Innovation Kvaerner's trouble to lead in
the second day of the third leg of the Whitbread round-the-world
yachting classic.
</P>
<P>
Toshiba led 1.8 nautical miles to another American entry,
Chessie Racing, on the 3,985-kilometer leg from Fremantle, Western
Australia, to Sydney, New South Wales.
</P>
<P>
In Sunday night, Norwegian boat Innovation Kvaerner fell into
rigging problem which threatened to bring down her mast, race
organisers said.
</P>
<P>
Nine yachts are competing in the nine-leg event on May 24 in
Southampton, England, where they started three months ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
