<HEADLINE> Turkish PM to Visit United States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Prime Minister Mesut
Yilmaz is to pay an official visit to the United States on
December 17-21, a Foreign Ministry spokesman announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a weekly press conference, Necati Utkan said that
"the visit will provide another opportunity to reaffirm the
friendly relations between the two countries."
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Yilmaz will hold talks with U.S. President
Bill Clinton at the White House on December 19, discussing
bilateral and multinational relations, Utkan said.
</P>
<P>
Yilmaz is also expected to meet with U.S. Vice President Al
Gore, Secretary of State Madeleine Albright and other
high-ranking officials, he added. 
</P>
