<HEADLINE> Chinese Film Festival Winners Named </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The Sixth Golden Rooster and
Hundred Flowers Film Festival ended here today.
</P>
<P>
This was the sixth year the China Golden Rooster Film Festival
and the Hundred Flower Film Festival had been combined into one
event.
</P>
<P>
"Opium War" was awarded Best Film honors at the 17th Golden
Rooster Festival, which has been under way in Foshan City in south
China's Guangdong province since Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"Three Sisters from Song's Family," jointly shot by studios
from Beijing and Hong Kong, won the award for Best Sino-Overseas
Jointly-Shot Film.
</P>
<P>
Liu Peiqi, starring in "Days without Hero" was named Best
Actor; Yu Hui, starring in "Xilian," Best Actress; and Wei Lian,
who directed "Strategic Turning-Point," Best Director.
</P>
<P>
The awards for the 20th Hundred Flowers Film Festival, which
were selected in November, were also announced here this evening.
</P>
<P>
The Best Actor and the Best Actress went to Gao Ming, who stars
in "Kong Fansen," and Ning Jing, who stars in "Red River Valley."
</P>
<P>
Three films tied for best ones: "Red River Valley," "Strategic
Turning-Point" and "Days without Hero." 
</P>
</TEXT>
