<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader Wei Jianxing Meets Indian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Wei Jianxing, member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau and member of the
Secretariat of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of
China (CPC), met here today with Indian President Kocheril Raman
Narayanan to discuss issues of mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the two sides agreed to maintain the
positive momentum in the development of bilateral relations and
further promote the establishment of a constructive and
cooperative partnership oriented toward the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
President Narayanan spoke highly of Chinese President Jiang
Zemin's historic visit to India in November last year, describing
it as "a new milestone" in Indian-Chinese relations, which has
opened up a new chapter in bilateral friendly cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Wei, who arrived here yesterday on a nine-day goodwill visit to
India at the invitation of Vice-President Krishna Kant, said
developing a stable, long-term good-neighborly friendship and
mutually beneficial cooperation with India is China's existing
policy.
</P>
<P>
A long-term and friendly cooperative relationship between China
and India is not only conducive to the economic and cultural
development of the two countries but also a great contribution to
peace in Asia and the world as a whole, he added.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Wei conveyed President Jiang's cordial
regards to President Narayanan and said the Chinese side expects
the Indian president to pay an early visit to China.
</P>
<P>
Besides, Indian Vice-President Kant held a banquet in honor of
Wei here this evening.  
</P>
</TEXT>
