<HEADLINE> Large Joint Brewery for Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, December 16 (Xinhua) -- A signing ceremony was held
here today for building a brewery with an annual production
capacity of 100,000 tons of beer in Shenzhen City, in south China's
Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
This is a joint effort of China's Qingdao Beer Company Ltd, a
Hong Kong-based company, and three Japanese corporations including
Asahi Breweries Ltd, involving a total investment of 52.73 million
US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Qingdao, Hong Kong and Japanese sides hold 35, 31 and 34
percent, respectively, of the shares for the Shenzhen Qingdao-Beer
Asahi Company Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture, which is located in Songgang town of
Shenzhen's Bao'an district, has begun being built, and is expected
to go into production in early 1999. 
</P>
