<HEADLINE> Pakistan Official Stresses Importance of Regional </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Minister of State
for Foreign Affairs Siddique Kanju said today that peace and
stability in the region is indispensable for the socio-economic
development for its one billion people.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with visiting Maldivian Minister of State for
Defense and National Security Abdul Sattar Anbaree, Kanju called
for a peaceful settlement of the Kashmir issue in accordance with
the U.N. Security Council resolutions, the Pakistani Foreign
Office said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
The Kashmir issue has festered for the past 50 years, Kanju
said, adding it is imperative to remove the underlying causes of
tension between Pakistan and India, the two major countries of the
region.
</P>
<P>
Regional peace and security will give a tremendous fillip to
the economic cooperation and contribute to the realization of the
economic potential of South Asia, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The Maldivian Minister of State expressed his satisfaction with
the ongoing cooperation between his country and Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
He said that his government hoped to further expand mutually
beneficial cooperation with Pakistan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
