<HEADLINE> China to Expedite Development of Information Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 16 (Xinhua) -- China is mapping an overall
plan to increase the use of information technology in all national
economic sectors, according to a three-day national conference on
information development which ended here today.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the State Council and leaders from all the
provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities gathered in
Shanghai to discuss national economic development through the use
of information technology.
</P>
<P>
Information advancement has so far become a major force for the
world's economic and social development. The whole country is
being called on to encourage digital technology and network
connections.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises are encouraged to increase the use of information
technologies as part of effort to motivate overall development of
similar industries.
</P>
<P>
The country has nearly 300,000 computers hooked up to the
Internet.  
</P>
