<HEADLINE>   Natural Gas Discovered Offshore Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Unocal Vietnam Exploration ltd,
a subsidiary of Unocal Corporation has discovered a significant
gas its first exploration well on block B offshore southwestern
Vietnam, a news release issued by Unocal corporation said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Two drill stem tests on the exploration well, B-KL-LX, yielded
a combined rate of 52.9 million cubic feet per day of gas from
Miocene Age sands in the Kim Long prospect.
</P>
<P>
Unocal Vietnam Exploration and its co-venturers signed a
production-sharing contract with Petrovietnam for block B in May
1996. Petrovietnam is Vietnam's only oil and gas enterprise.
</P>
<P>
Unocal is a leading global energy resource and project
development company.
</P>
<P>
Block B covers more than 1.3 million acres (5,263 square
kilometers). It lies in the northern part of the Malay basin in
approximately 180-245 feet (55-75 meters) of water. The block is
300 miles west-southwest of Vietnam's Vung Tau and 150 miles east
of Songkhla, Thailand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
