<HEADLINE> France to Build Model of Territorial Planning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The French government decided
Tuesday to build the central region of the Massif Central into a
model of good territorial planning with projects of lasting
development in industry, transport and agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The Minister of Environment and Territorial Planning, Dominique
Voynet, said the government will spend 350 million francs (58
million U.S. dollars) in 1998 and 1999 to support the development
projects.
</P>
<P>
The projects will focus on work involving pottery, polishing,
biological agriculture, the breeding of grass-eating cattle, and
the production of cheese, vegetables and wood, the latter for
industrial use and energy.
</P>
<P>
Plans involve several local railways linking the regional
capital Clermont-Ferrand with Paris and Lyon, and expressways to
be built or expanded.
</P>
<P>
At a inter-ministerial session on a new law on territorial
planning, Prime Minister Lionel Jospin said that the purpose of
territorial planning is the creation of more jobs.
</P>
<P>
Voynet said the new law will serve national solidarity, durable
planning and development, and be a model within the European
Union. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
