<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany, Ukraine to Expand Defense Technology Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Germany and Ukraine signed a
framework accord Tuesday aimed at intensifying bilateral
cooperation in defense technology.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed in Bonn during a meeting between
visiting Ukrainian Defense Minister Oleksandr Kusmuk and his
German counterpart, Volker Ruehe.
</P>
<P>
The first concrete step to implement the agreement could be
possible cooperation by the European Airbus Industry consortium,
Ukraine and Russia to jointly develop and manufacture a large
military transport aircraft, dubbed the Future Transport Aircraft,
the German defense ministry said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The first feasibility talks on the project would be held within
the next few days, the statement added.
</P>
<P>
Kusmuk also briefed Ruehe on Ukraine's plan to cut its armed
forces from 386,000 to 350,000 by the year 2005. They also agreed
to continue the existing cooperation between the two armed
forces. Germany was expected to invite 20 Ukrainian officers for
military training in Germany next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
