<HEADLINE> Italian and Russian Win in Ski Racing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Italian Fulvio Valbusa won the
men's 15-kilometer freestyle ski race in the Nordic World Cup,
while Russian Larissa Lazutina took the women's title on Tuesday
in Trente, Italy.
</P>
<P>
Valbusa led all the way to victory, ahead of defending overall
leader Norwegian Bjorn Daehlie with a time of 37 minutes and 4.30
seconds.
</P>
<P>
Another Norwegian Thomas Alsgaad finished second with the race
favorite Daehlie third, 13.5 seconds and 29 seconds behind the
Italian repectively, the pair shared the first two spots in the
overall standings.
</P>
<P>
Lazutina timed 37 minutes and 40.4 seconds for her second
victory in the season, 30.9 seconds ahead of Italian rookie Sabina
Valbusa.
</P>
<P>
Former Olympic and world champion Stefania Belmondo of Italy
finished third, clocking 38:14.3.
</P>
<P>
Bente Martinsen of Norway placed 25th in Tuesday's race but the
mark has no threat to her overall leading on the standings with
286 points.
</P>
<P>
The Russian closed in as the runner-up on the standings, 26
points short of Martinsen, while another Norwegian Anita
Moen-Guidon is far behind with just 185 points. 
</P>
