<HEADLINE> Southernmost Province Starts Rectifying Financial Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Hainan, the southernmost
province in China, today launched a campaign to rectify local
financial industry by closing down five banking institutions and
abolishing another 28 financial bodies.
</P>
<P>
It is a strategic move by the Hainan Provincial Branch of the
People's Bank of China and the island province to restore the
order of the local financial sector and to avoid financial hazards.
</P>
<P>
The People's Urban Credit Cooperative of Haikou City and other
four local banking institutions have been found to have disturbed
local financial order by raising the interest rates in various
forms to lure depositors.
</P>
<P>
The leading officials in the five credit cooperatives will
receive administrative and financial punishment, while the
cooperatives' rights and debts as well as businesses have been
trusted to the Hainan Development Bank.
</P>
<P>
The other 28 banking institutions, which have been canceled,
have been merged into the bank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
