<HEADLINE> China to Modernize Taxation System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 16 (Xinhua) -- China's taxation departments
should further ideological emancipation and reforms, so as to set
up a modernized taxation system to meet the requirements of
developing the socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
Xiang Huaicheng, Deputy Director of the State Administration of
Taxation (SAT), made the call at today's National Conference on
Taxation. Financial Minister and SAT Director Liu Zhongli were
present at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
China has made remarkable breakthroughs in restructuring
its taxation system and the administration of the sector has been
reinforced, Xiang said, but noting that the present management
level is yet to meet the needs of the market economy and modern
taxation system.
</P>
<P>
The official called for efforts to improve the operation the
taxation sector, in a bid to make it more standardized, more
scientific and more institutionalized.
</P>
<P>
All institutions or individuals who have broken the law on
taxation must be punished in line with the law, he stressed.
</P>
