<HEADLINE> State Councillor: Modernization Requires Skilled Personnel (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 16 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese official said
here today that the key to the success of China's modernization
drive is fostering a large number of highly competent skilled
workers.
</P>
<P>
State Councillor Li Guixian made the remarks at the opening
ceremony of a national conference organized by the Ministry of
Personnel.
</P>
<P>
"Skilled personnel is a resource of utmost importance to
economic growth and social progress," Li said. "Whether we can
foster a large number of high-quality laborers and specialists and
bring our advantage of a huge human resource into full play will
decide our country's destiny in the next century."
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that by the end of 1995 China had a population
of 44.65 million people who either received education in at least
a technical secondary school or possessed a primary professional
title.
</P>
<P>
Among those people categorized as "skilled personnel" according
to Chinese standards, only 8.85 million had senior or intermediate
professional titles.
</P>
<P>
"At present, there remains a serious shortage of skilled
personnel in our country," Li said. "And due to an imbalance of
personnel distribution in different sectors and regions, a large
portion of our limited resource of skilled personnel has been
wasted."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
