pier in south China's Guangdong Province, the first of its kind in
the country, has handled more than 10 million tons of crude oil
after three years of operation.
</P>
<P>
The floating pier has helped the Maoming Petrochemical Company
build up the country's first 10-million-ton oil refinery.
</P>
<P>
The construction and operation of the pier have helped save
more than 300 million yuan in expenditures compared with the
traditional fixed wharfs, officials said.
</P>
<P>
At a cost of more than 600 million yuan, the pier was jointly
built in 1994 by the Maoming Petrochemical Company and a petroleum
company from Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The pier has so far accommodated 65 super-tankers from a number
of countries in West Asia. 
