<HEADLINE> China, Philippines Satisfied With Bilateral Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister
Qian Qichen and his Philippine counterpart, Domingo Siazon, today
expressed their satisfaction with the development of the relations
between their two countries.
</P>
<P>
They shared the view that exchanges and contacts in various
fields between China and the Philippines are increasing day by day
and bilateral economic and trade cooperation maintains a good
development momentum. But there exists more potential and the two
governments should encourage enterprises of the two countries to
seek new ways for cooperation and for increasing mutual
investments, they pointed out.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting here, the two ministers also expressed the view
that after Hong Kong returned to China, chances for cooperation
between China and the Philippines have increased.
</P>
<P>
Both Qian and Siazon are here for an informal summit of East
Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
On the South China Sea issue, Siazon said that on the whole,
the area has remained peaceful since April this year and this is
conducive to the relations and the enhancement of trust between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Qian agreed with Siazon's view on the issue.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers also exchanged views on other issues of
common concern.  
</P>
</TEXT>
