<HEADLINE> Shanghai Outlines Building Materials Development Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's leading
manufacturing center, has mapped out a plan for vigorously
developing the building materials industry in the next three years.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan, the city will advance development of
seven major building materials which will include new-type wall
materials, chemical building materials, concrete, processed glass,
and glass wool.
</P>
<P>
Local experts explained that in its efforts to expand building
materials industry, Shanghai would mainly improve economic
performance of enterprises, develop more building materials
featuring land-saving, energy- and water-efficient, recycled use
of discarded materials by way of relying on science and
technology. The city plans to raise its technology in the building
materials industry to the advanced world level.
</P>
<P>
By the year of 2000, the building materials sector of Shanghai
is expected to generate 48.4 billion yuan of output value, more
than triple the 1995 figure, and to earn 1.2 billion U.S. dollars
from exports.
</P>
<P>
The city has also decided to set aside three billion yuan for
development and production of new building materials, and set up
more large professional building materials conglomerates and
increase cooperation with overseas companies in jointly developing
new building materials in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The city will also carry out technical upgrading of small and
medium-sized enterprises in this field, shut down some
energy-consuming, inefficient and pollution-causing cement plants
and enlarge cement output by relying on application of new
technology, said local sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
