<HEADLINE> About 2,593 Athletes Expected At Nagano Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Nagano Organising Committee
Tuesday said a record 2,593 athletes from 67 countries and regions
are planning to compete in next February's Winter Olympics in
Nagano, Japan.
</P>
<P>
The United States will send the largest team -- 207 athletes --
followed by host Japan with 166 and Switzerland 163.
</P>
<P>
The number of countries attending is equal to the record number
set at the Lillehammer Games four years ago.
</P>
<P>
More athletes were expected in Nagano because three new sports
were added -- women's ice hockey, curling and snowboarding.
</P>
<P>
Organisers also said the number of competitors was likely to
fall slightly as some of the athletes had yet to met minimum
qualification standards set by international sports federations.
