<HEADLINE> OAU Chief Appeals to Bring Justice to Genocide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Salim Ahmed Salim,
secretary general of the Organization of African Unity (OAU),
today firmly condemned the recent massacre of refugees in Rwanda
and appealed to bring the genocide suspects to justice.
</P>
<P>
An OAU press release issued here said Salim expressed shock
over the recent massacre of refugees in Mudende Refugee Camp near
Gisenyi in Rwanda, and urged that all the necessary measures
should be taken to ensure suspects are brought to justice, within
the context of the International Criminal Tribunal for Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
"At a time when the international community has been
encouraging the Rwandan government in its efforts at promoting
national reconciliation, this cowardly and brutal act has come as
a sad blow," he noted.
</P>
<P>
The secretary general urged OAU member states and the
international community not to give refuge to genocide suspects.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed condolences to the governments and peoples
of Rwanda and the Democratic Republic of Congo. 
</P>
