<HEADLINE> US-Kuwait Navy Maneuvers Start in Kuwaiti Waters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Naval forces from
Kuwait and the United States started a joint military exercise
today in Kuwaiti waters north of Umm Al-Maraden Island.
</P>
<P>
The naval maneuvers code-named "Eager-98/1" were aimed at
upgrading the combat skills of the Kuwaiti soldiers by taking
advantage of the U.S. navy experience, according to Kuwait
News Agency (KUNA).
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted a Kuwaiti military source as saying that the
maneuvers were joined by 400 U.S. navy soldiers, five speed boats
and a number of amphibious tanks and some Kuwaiti marine patrol
boats and soldiers.
</P>
<P>
This might be the last joint military exercises between the
small Gulf state and the United States before the end of this year
which has seen several military training exercises and maneuvers
according to a defense agreement signed between the two countries
following the Gulf War in 1991.
</P>
<P>
The KUNA did not say how long the maneuvers would last.
</P>
