<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader Meets Australian Governor-General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Canberra, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese leader Li
Ruihuan today expressed China's readiness to make joint efforts
with Australia to push the relations between the two countries to
a new high in the next 25 years.
</P>
<P>
"China is willing to work together with Australia to write a
more splendid chapter in the next 25 years in Sino-Australian ties
by adhering to the principle of mutual respect, equality, mutual
benefit and seeking common ground while reserving differences and
taking a broad and long-term view and working in a down-to-earth
manner," Li, chairman of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference National Committee, said here when meeting
with Australian Governor-General William Deane.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Li conveyed Chinese President Jiang Zemin's
sincere regards to the governor-general and invited him to visit
China at his convenience.
</P>
<P>
Li also expressed his satisfaction with the smooth development
of the relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
All-round and substantial progress has been made during the
past 25 years since China and Australia established diplomatic
relations thanks to the joint efforts of the governments and
people of the two countries, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Deane said he was very pleased that on the eve of the 25th
anniversary of the establishment of Sino-Australian diplomatic
ties, Li, at the invitation of the Australian government, is
visiting Australia and celebrating the significant day together
with the Australian people.
</P>
<P>
The Australian government and people attach importance to and
cherish the friendly ties with China, Deane said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his belief that the good Australian-Chinese ties
will enjoy further development in the next century.
</P>
<P>
Li and his party arrived in Canberra, capital of Australia,
today from Melbourne, the second largest city in the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
