<HEADLINE> ADB Approves Loan to India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) today approved a 150 million U.S. dollar loan to India for a
gas pipeline project, the Press Trust of India reported today.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement issued by the Philippines-based bank,
the loan will be used for the construction of a pipeline system to
transport liquefied natural gas from western India to the north.
</P>
<P>
The bank is also expected to help the gas authority of India
arrange parallel co-financing for the 364 million dollar project,
the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The loan is payable in 15 years including a four-year grace
period. 
</P>
