<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader on CPPCC Role </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Li cited CPPCC's functions as political consultation,
democratic supervision and participation in political affairs
while briefing Speaker Robert Halverson of the Australian House of
Representative and President Margaret Reid of the Australian
Senate on China's system of multi-party cooperation and political
consultation under the leadership of the Chinese Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
Li, who is on a six-day visit to Australia, met with the two
leaders of the Australian Parliament here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
He told the top legislators that CPPCC made great contributions
to the founding of New China in 1949 and is now playing a
significant role in carrying out the current reform and
modernization drive, safeguarding the country's stability and
integrity, promoting its socialist democratic and legislative
development and pushing forward the cause of its peaceful
reunification.
</P>
<P>
CPPCC is committed to peace and development in the world
through energetically advancing friendship and cooperation with
people in various countries, Li said.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say CPPCC would like to join the efforts of all
peace-loving organizations and people to bring a peaceful, stable
and prosperous world into the next century.  
