<HEADLINE> Nigeria's New Cabinet Formed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's head of state General
Sani Abacha last night named a 33-member Federal Executive
Council or cabinet, with 16 former ministers of the dissolved
cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Of the 16 former ministers in the new cabinet, 10 retained
their former portfolios while six were swapped portfolios.
</P>
<P>
They are expected to be sworn in by the head of state on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Abacha sacked the former cabinet a month ago to ensure the
success of the transition to civil rule program and give an
opportunity to cabinet members to contest in the elections.
</P>
<P>
The head of state has also approved the appointment of eight
ambassadors expected to go to such European countries as Germany,
France, Spain, Ireland, Belgium, Sweden, tahe Netherlands and
Austria. 
