<HEADLINE> Economic Research Center Set up in Lusaka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LUSAKA, December 16 (Xinhua) -- A team of Zambian
professionals have set up a research center in Lusaka to deal
with socio-economic, public policy advocacy and related issues#,
Zambia Daily Mail reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Center for Policy Research and Analysis is a non-profit
making and independent organization headed by Lusaka businessman
Bernard Chisanga, former chief executive of the Zambia
Association of Chambers of Commerce and Industry.
</P>
<P>
The center's priorities are to apply advocacy for sustainable
economic development in the social dimensions of Zambia's
macro-economic transformation policies and programs, democratic
governance and multiparty democracy, environmental management and
sustainable development, according to the local newspaper.
</P>
<P>
It quoted Chisanga as saying that the center will undertake
empirical research and comprehensive surveys and that the
findings will be presented to decision makers and society's
stakeholders to influence public direction and democratic
governance on the ground. 
</P>
