<HEADLINE> Sino-ASEAN Relations Enter New Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The Joint Statement of the
Summit of the People's Republic of China and the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) marks a new stage of Sino-ASEAN
relations, Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman Tang Guoqiang said.
</P>
<P>
Tang made the remarks here in today's news briefing when asked
to comment on the informal summit of China, Japan, the Republic of
Korea and ASEAN, and that of China and ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
He said the informal summits, a gathering of the leaders of the
east Asian nations, were the first top-level meetings between
China and those nations.
</P>
<P>
During the meetings, leaders expressed their optimism on the
region's development in the 21st century, and exchanged views on
strengthening the cooperation between east Asian nations in
regional and international affairs before reaching an extensive
agreement, he said.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin put forward at the summits China's
principle of strengthening cooperation in the region, and
exchanged extensive views with ASEAN leaders on the relationship
between China and the association, Tang said.
</P>
<P>
Tang referred to the joint statement of the Sino-ASEAN summit
that the two sides passed as important fruit, which not only
determined the principle to guide relations between the two sides,
but also decided that the common goal in their policies is to
establish a good-neighbor partnership of mutual trust in the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
He stated that those summits would not only benefit the
economic growth of Asia and advance their mutually beneficial
cooperation, but they also would intensify the friendly and
cooperative links between China and ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
These links will have an important and far-reaching influence
on the 21st century's development of east Asia and of the
Sino-ASEAN good-neighbor partnership of mutual trust, he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
