<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Improving The Administration Of Justice In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The administration of justice
in China has improved in the last five years, according to Ren
Jianxin, the president of the Supreme People's Court.
</P>
<P>
Since 1993, China's courts have settled more than 20 million
cases, 14.73 percent more each year, on average, Ren said, and Law
appeals between January and October of this year were down 9.54
percent from the same time five years ago.
</P>
<P>
Some 97 percent of cases have been finished within the time
allotted by the law, he said, explaining, "Our courts have greatly
improved their efficiency and overall quality of case-handling."
</P>
<P>
Various courts have also finished 18 million civil, economic,
maritime and administrative cases over the past five years,
involving about 850 billion yuan in property, or 102.4 billion US
dollars, he said.
</P>
<P>
There has also been a reform in civil and economic trial
procedure in the court system. The Law on Judges went into effect
on July 1, 1995.
</P>
<P>
In the five-year period, 122 courts were awarded prizes and 93
judges won awards by the Supreme People's Court, Ren said.
</P>
<P>
By November, China had 33 agreements on justice assistance with
25 countries and regions, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971216.0086 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Markets in Central China More Mature </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 16 (Xinhua) -- After years of construction,
market places in east China's Anhui Province have grown more
mature and specialized, according to sources with the provincial
Administrative Bureau of Industry and Commerce.
</P>
<P>
Statistics by the bureau show that the province now has more
than 4,100 diversified markets, which handle trade worth 56
billion yuan (6.7 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Of the total, five markets each have an annual trade volume
exceeding one billion yuan (120 million dollars), and 48 ones each
exceeding 100 million yuan (12 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
More than 870 of the markets in the province are specialized,
which have greatly helped the development of relevant production
in localities. There are also large markets which have grown
toward potential business centers integrating services of
warehouse storage, information consultancy and catering industries.
</P>
<P>
Market development in Anhui also features rational
distribution. Agricultural and sideline product markets are close
to production bases, while most of industrial product markets are
located in cities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
