<HEADLINE> China's Diplomatic Results Viewed as Fruitful in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Ministry spokesman
Tang Guoqiang reviewed China's diplomatic work in 1997 at today's
news conference, saying that China's independent foreign policy of
peace has resulted in abundant achievements.
</P>
<P>
China's smooth resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over
Hong Kong in accordance with the "one country, two system" policy
was an important step forward in the nation's reunification, Tang
said.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin, Premier Li Peng and other Chinese
Communist Party or government officials visited more than 60
countries on five continents this year, he said, and more than 30
heads of state or government leaders visited China. This shows
that China's friendship and cooperation with the rest of the world
is deepening, Tang said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China's good-neighbor relationship with
surrounding countries has improved, cooperation with other
developing countries has been consolidated and relationships with
western developed countries have been upgraded.
</P>
<P>
"China has actively participated in multilateral diplomacy and
regional coordination, played a unique and constructive role in
both international and regional affairs, and made its own
contributions to the cause of world peace and development," Tang
said. 
