<HEADLINE> Unexploded Bombs Dug Up in Downtown Area of Chinese Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 16 (Xinhua) -- More than 2,500 bomb-like
devices were unearthed in the downtown area of Beijing during
construction work, according to today's "Beijing Youth Daily".
</P>
<P>
Initial analysis shows that the 20-centimeter rusty devices
were bombs for military use but it remains unknown who made them
and when they were made, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Construction workers unearthed the devices while laying the
cable near a block of flats in a southern district of the city
recently.
</P>
<P>
Police were called to remove them, and a bomb squad will
dispose of them, the report said.
</P>
<P>
This is the largest amount of explosives to be found in Beijing
since it became the capital of the People's Republic of China in
1949, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
