<HEADLINE> China Begins Construction of Fourth Nuclear Power Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIANYUNGANG, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Construction of China's
fourth nuclear power plant -- Lianyungang nuclear power station --
has started recently in east China's Jiangsu province.
</P>
<P>
According to an agreement signed by the Chinese and Russian
governments in 1996, the Chinese government has made preparations
for the construction work.
</P>
<P>
A feasibility report on the plant was approved by experts in
Beijing on December 1, and has been submitted for approval from
the State Council.
</P>
<P>
With a total investment of 20 million yuan, the first
on-the-spot construction program covers a provisional water supply
system which will serve the construction of the plant.
</P>
<P>
The project, including an 11-kilometer-long water pipe, is
expected to complete in two months. 
