<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Singapore Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin today described the exchange and cooperation in various
areas between China and Singapore as active and mutually
beneficial.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with Singapore Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong here, Jiang
said that in recent years, the Sino-Singapore relations have
maintained a good development trend.
</P>
<P>
Goh said the economic and trade cooperation between the two
countries is good and Singapore attaches special importance to the
cooperative projects between the two countries in the Suzhou
Industrial Park in China. He expressed the hope that the two sides
cooperate closely to solve the existing problems of the projects.
</P>
<P>
Jiang and Goh, both in Malaysia to attend an informal summit of
East Asian countries, also discussed the current financial turmoil
in Southeast Asian nations.
</P>
<P>
Goh noted that the difficulties faced by some ASEAN countries
have had unavoidable impacts on other ASEAN countries. He called
for efforts to actively seek ways and means to solve the problems
and hoped that China would play its role in this regard.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said, "The reason behind the financial turbulence is
complex. We understand the difficulties some countries are facing.
The financial turbulence has taught us a lesson: Economic security
should cover financial security and while a country is opening up,
it needs to maintain its own rational economic structure and
coordinated development of infrastructure and manufacturing."
</P>
<P>
"We have confidence in the future of the economy in Asia,"
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Both leaders also gave positive assessments to the East Asian
summit which concluded here today.  
</P>
</TEXT>
