<HEADLINE> Macao-Zhuhai Bridge Under Design </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The planned bridge to link
Macao and Zhuhai City, south China's Guangdong Province, is under
design and the construction work is expected to begin in April
1998.
</P>
<P>
The Macao Daily News reported today that the China-Portugal
Infrastructure Coordination Commission will pick one of the two
designs currently being conducted in Macao and China's inland
areas.
</P>
<P>
The design by a subsidiary of the Profabril Group Company is
said to have been favored by the commission, the report said.
</P>
<P>
A group of experts from China's Ministry of Communications and
departments in Guangdong Province and Zhuhai City studied the
feasibility report and finished a hydrological survey near the
site of the proposed bridge not long ago.
</P>
<P>
The coordination commission said that construction of the
bridge will begin next April, and be completed in November
1999. Running more than 1,100 meters long, the Macao-Zhuhai Bridge
will cost 250 million patacas (31.3 million US dollars).
</P>
</TEXT>
