<HEADLINE> HK's Fairwood Vows to Expand Fast Food Outlet Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The Fairwood Holdings
Limited (Fairwood), a leading fast food chain in Hong Kong,
announced today that the company will continue to expand its
operations in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
In response to rumors reported in certain local media, Dennis
Lo, managing director of Fairwood said: "Our expansion plan in
Hong Kong has never stopped."
</P>
<P>
In the financial year ending March 31,1998, Fairwood plans to
open eight new fast food outlets, and up to now, four have been
opened and three others have been committed, Lo said.
</P>
<P>
"By the end of this financial year, we will have a total of
approximately 100 outlets in Hong Kong," Lo added.
</P>
<P>
"In view of our expanding operation, we are still recruiting
qualified staff, to provide the best services to our customers,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Fairwood has opened eight new institutional
catering outlets this year, making the total number 11.
</P>
<P>
The company will continue to penetrate this sector of business
in order to diversify the income base of the company.
</P>
<P>
"We are confident of the prospects of the company since cost
control and restructuring of the company's business have shown
positive effect. We would like to reassure our customers and
shareholders our commitment in the fast food business," Lo said.
</P>
