<HEADLINE> Four New Chinese Ambassadors Appointed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
has appointed four new ambassadors in accordance with a decision
of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
Zhai Jun was appointed the new ambassador to Libya, replacing
Qin Hongguo.
</P>
<P>
Song Zengshou was appointed the new ambassador to Uganda,
replacing Tan Xingju.
</P>
<P>
Chen Laiyuan was appointed the new ambassador to Lesotho,
replacing Lin Tinghai.
</P>
<P>
Zheng Jinjiong was appointed the new ambassador to Ireland,
replacing Fan Huijuan (female). 
</P>
