<HEADLINE> Northeast China Province Grows Fast in Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province has received 1.2 million overseas tourists in the past
five years, earning a total of foreign exchange of 800 million US
dollars, 2.2 and 2.5 times that of the five years before 1992,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Chen Xi, director of the provincial tourism bureau, said that
foreign exchange earnings by tourism has become the province's
important source of non-trade foreign exchange revenue. He also
indicated that Liaoning has received 17,000 overseas Chinese
tourists since 1992.
</P>
<P>
Unique scenic spots like Hongshan culture relics, Jiumenkou --
a section of China's Great Wall on the sea, and Benxi Shuidong --
Asia's longest subterranean river, have attracted overseas
tourists from over 35 countries and areas.
</P>
<P>
Chen said that Liaoning has protected and improved tourism
environment by developing tourism attractions. Up to now, the
province has 78 state-level and 179 provincial-level scenic spots.
</P>
<P>
Tourism has become Liaoning's pilot industry. With expansion of
tourism industry scale, the province's reception capacity has also
improvement.
</P>
<P>
It now has 175 hotels and restaurants mainly for overseas
guests, 2.4 times that in 1991. The province has 189 travel
agencies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
