<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Fatal Accidents Involving Tu-154 in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The following are deadly
accidents involving the Tu-154 in recent years. The three-engined
medium range plane was made by the former Soviet Union.
</P>
<P>
-- A Tajik-owned Tu-154 crashed near Sharjah, UAE, Monday
night, killing 85 people.
</P>
<P>
-- A Tu-154 crashed into the mountain on the Norwegian island
of Spitsbergen on August 29, 1996, killing 141 people.
</P>
<P>
-- In December 1995, all 97 aboard a Tu-154 were killed in a
crash in Russia's Far East.
</P>
<P>
-- In January 1994, a Tu-154 crash in Siberia, killing all 125
aboard.
</P>
<P>
-- In June 1994, a Tu-154 crashed in Xi'an, Western China,
killing all 160 aboard.


16/12/97 9:20 GMT

=12161018
NNNN
17:24 17:24 g # PAB
</P>
