<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southwest Chinese Province Regulates Commodity Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Sichuan Province in southwest
China has recently adopted regulations on commodity market to
strengthen the legal system in this respect.
</P>
<P>
According to the "Regulations on the Management of Sichuan
Province's Commodity Market," legal market activity will be
protected; no organizations or individuals can meddle normal
activities of the commodity market, and traders should have
necessary licenses to enter market.
</P>
<P>
The regulations also clearly prohibit illegal market activities
like cheating and driving up prices.
</P>
<P>
The regulations will be put into force on January 1, 1998.
</P>
</TEXT>
