<HEADLINE> Share Prices Plunge Sharply on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined
sharply on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index lost another 38.89 points to close at 1,561.75
points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume stood at 194.81 million units, valued
at 415.46 million Singapore dollars (about 248.78 million U.S.
dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 280 to 67, while 261
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Telecom was the most actively traded counter as
it registered a turnover of 9.97 million units. It was followed by
Singapore Technologies Engineering which had 7.76 million shares
traded. Rekapac was next with 7.09 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 50 cents to finish at 22 Singapore dollars.
Elec, Roth S. and SPH increased by 20 cents to end at 4.26 U.S.
dollars, 8.8 Singapore dollars, and 15.8 Singapore dollars
respectively. City Developments picked up by 15 cents to close at
7.15 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Venture Warrant9907 was the biggest loser as
it declined by 1.9 dollars to end at 2.9 Singapore dollars. Local
beverage and food maker F&AMP;N fell by 1.1 dollars to close at 6.75
Singapore dollars, while the OCBC (Overseas Chinese Banking
Corporation) Foreign and the UOB (United Overseas Bank) Foreign
dropped by 60 cents each to finish at 9.1 and 9.2 Singapore
dollars respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
