<HEADLINE> More Air Routes to Three Gorges Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The Three Gorges Airport in
Yichang City in China's Hubei Province started its connections with
Kunming and Qingdao this morning, expanding its links to 14 cities.
</P>
<P>
The destinations include Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou, Chengdu,
and Changsha, with a total of 110 scheduled flights every week.
</P>
<P>
Since China started the construction of the Three Gorges
Project on the middle reach of the Yangtze River, the government
has invested heavily in the development of high-speed
transportation to the area.
</P>
<P>
People in Beijing can now fly directly to the Three Gorges
Airport in an hour and a half. The airport can handle 1.4 million
passengers annually. It opened in 1996 after two years of
construction work. 
</P>
