<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Largest Stibium Mine Free From Silicosis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The life expectancy of the
10,000 miners working at the world's largest stibium mine in
Xikuangshan in central China's Hunan Province has been lifted from
30 in 1949 to 68 today.
</P>
<P>
The Xikuangshan mine used to be plagued by silicosis, a disease
caused by the intake of dusts.
</P>
<P>
Experts said the high incidence of the disease was caused by
poor ventilation. Statistics showed that from 1897 to 1949 the
disease claimed 90,000 lives.
</P>
<P>
In Tongjiayuan Village near the mine, about 120 men died of
silicosis.
</P>
<P>
Since the start of the 1950s, the local government has invested
large amounts of money to improve the ventilation facilities of
the mine. The content of dust in the air has been cut to within
two milligrams per cubic meter.
</P>
<P>
Xikuangshan's first hospital specialized in curing silicosis,
built in 1951, could only hospitalize a dozen patients. Since then
the mine has built several other hospitals, and improved their
medical instruments.
</P>
<P>
The local government allocates 250,000 yuan (about 30,000 US
dollars) every year to organize physical check-ups among the
miners.
</P>
<P>
The incidence of silicosis has dropped to under one
percent. According to statistics, there have been only 57 cases of
silicosis reported in the mine since 1958.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971216.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Scientists Develop Advanced Cotton Pickers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists have
successfully developed advanced self-propelled cotton picker
and the two sample cotton pickers have undergone smooth
trial operation in four hectares of cotton fields in Xinjiang,
one of China major cotton producers in Northwest China.
</P>
<P>
Experts here said that the cotton pickers, called "4MZ-2
Self-Propelled Picker" and "4MX-2 Cotton Picker" could pick up
more than 90 percent cotton in the cotton fields and they are up
to the same level of foreign ones in terms of technical
indicators.
</P>
<P>
The development of the advanced cotton pickers are listed
among major science and technology projects of the State Science
and Technology Commission during the country's ninth five-year
development plan period (1996 to 2000).
</P>
<P>
They estimated that one newly developed cotton picker could do
as much work as that of 300 or 400 cotton picking workers.
</P>
<P>
Scientists from Xinjiang Academy of Agricultural Science,
Xinjiang Agricultural University, China Agro-Technical Institute
have spent more than one year for the development of cotton
pickers.
</P>
<P>
They said 70 percent of parts of self-propelled cotton
picker is made in China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971216.0135 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT December 16 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin and leaders of
the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) Tuesday agreed
to enhance cooperation between China and ASEAN as well as between
China and individual ASEAN member states.
</P>
<P>
In a joint statement issued following their meeting, the
leaders agreed to heighten cooperation at bilateral and
multilateral levels in promoting economic growth, sustainable
development and social progress on the basis of equality and
mutual benefit. (China-ASEAN-Statement)
</P>
