<P>
MINSK -- Belarus's Prime Minister Sergei Ling said Sunday that
Belarus plans to cooperate with the United States based on the
principles of "equality and mutual benefit."
</P>
<P>
Ling made the remark during the U.S. delegation's visit to
Belarus. He stressed that enhancing foreign cooperation is crucial
to the country's economy, and Belarus has an open economy, with
two thirds of its production exported. He emphasized that Belarus
has played a "role of stability" in eastern Europe. Belarus will
seek to resolve all problems with the U.S. through "the way of
civilization," he said. (Belarus-U.S.-Cooperation)
</P>
