<P>
WUHAN -- China will invest two billion yuan in building a
national command system on flood and drought control, an official
from the Ministry of Water Resources said here today.
</P>
<P>
The system covers information collection, tele-communications,
automatic forecast and a computer network. Formation of the system
will help the nation's flood control headquarters to gain a
quicker and better understanding of floods in all parts of the
country and will pave the way for building a nationwide
hydrological data system, the official said. (China-Command System)
 
