<HEADLINE> Shandong to Phase Out Small Thermal Power Plants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Fangzhi Thermal Power Plant, the
oldest power plant in east China's Shandong Province, has been
closed down for the sake of environmental protection, the
Beijing-based "China Youth News" reported.
</P>
<P>
The first-ever-taken move to shut down a smoothly-operating
power plant was part of the efforts made by the provincial
government to maintain sustainable development, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The Fangzhi Power Plant has five generating sets, with a total
generating capacity of 42,000 kilowatts. The province has 193 such
high energy consuming, polluting thermal power plants, which are
inefficient and harmful to the environment.
</P>
<P>
Another small thermal power plant is expected to be closed down
in the first half of next year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
