<HEADLINE> Russian Boy Slashed to Death in Zanzibar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, December 16 (Xinhua) -- A 16-year old boy, son
of a Russian female national working with a United Nations
Development Program-funded project at the Ministry of Health, was
killed on Monday in Zanzibar.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses and neighbors said the victim, identified as Alex, was
burnt after he had been slashed with knives by his assailants,
reported "Daily News" today.
</P>
<P>
Neighbors said yesterday that unknown persons riding a
motorcycle had gone inside a house at about 9 a.m. After they had
gone out, they saw heavy smoke coming out of the house at Mombasa
area.
</P>
<P>
Suspecting a fire outbreak or an electricity fault, the
neighbors informed the fire brigade and the police. But when the
police and neighbors reached the house they found the body was
inflicted with deep cuts.
</P>
<P>
The body was flown by a chartered plane yesterday afternoon to
Dar es Salaam for further arrangements to transport the body to
Russia for burial.
</P>
<P>
The Director of Criminal Investigations of Zanzibar, has
confirmed the grisly murder, but declined to comment.
</P>
<P>
Neighbors and friends were seen at the residence
of the deceased in a show of sympathy with the bereaved family.
Neighbors said they heard the mother of the deceased wailing
that the boy had once confided to her some people had vowed to
teach him a lesson. 
</P>
</TEXT>
