<HEADLINE> First Group of National-Level Restaurants Chosen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The first group of 36
national-level restaurants have been chosen through a year-long
assessment, according to officials attending a ceremony to grant
certificates held here yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Some 300 restaurants from across the country participated in
the assessment. All the 36 restaurants are large and medium-sized
ones, which can accommodate 350 to 2,000 people at a time.
</P>
<P>
Among them are the Qianmen (Beijing) Branch of Quanjude Roast
Duck Restaurant, the Shanghai-based Meixing Restaurant and the
Guangzhou Restaurant. Their annual turnover ranges from 20 million
yuan to 30 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The assessment was in line with a state regulation concerning
the grading of restaurants and hotels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
