<HEADLINE> ASEAN, Japan Resolve to Advance Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 16 (Xinhua) -- ASEAN and Japan today
pledged to further their cooperation towards the 21st century,
with a view to achieving a more profound and wide-ranging
relationship.
</P>
<P>
In a joint statement issued after the ASEAN-Japan informal
summit held here today, ASEAN and Japanese leaders decided to
intensify dialogues and exchanges at all levels to forge an
enhanced partnership.
</P>
<P>
They said priority in their cooperation would be given to
addressing market access issues and structural changes in the
industrial sector to promote balanced growth of ASEAN-Japan trade.
</P>
<P>
