facilitation of trade by promoting such activities as those in the
World Trade Organization, taking into account the economic
situations of developing countries, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
They said priority would also be accorded to enhancing ASEAN's
competitiveness through various ways including modernizing small
and medium enterprises and strengthening supporting industries.
</P>
<P>
Both sides also pledged to promote macro-economic and financial
stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
The leaders decided to hold their meetings as frequently as
possible.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN (Association of Southeast Asian Nations) groups Brunei,
Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, the Philippines, Singapore,
Thailand and Vietnam.  
