<HEADLINE> China to Build National Flood &AMP; Drought Command System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, December 16 (Xinhua) -- China will invest two billion
yuan in building a national command system on flood and drought
control, an official from the Ministry of Water Resources said
here today.
</P>
<P>
The system covers information collection, tele-communications,
automatic forecast and a computer network.
</P>
<P>
Formation of the system will help the nation's flood control
headquarters to gain a quicker and better understanding of floods
in all parts of the country and will pave the way for building a
nationwide hydrological data system, the official said.
</P>
<P>
China is a country vulnerable to floods and drought, which pose
a serious threat to China's most populous areas and many
economically-developed regions. In each of the past few years, the
country suffered economic losses of more than 100 billion yuan
caused by floods alone. 
</P>
