<HEADLINE> Railway Offers Huge Business Opportunity for Overseas Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, December 16 (Xinhua) -- China needs 100 billion
yuan to build industrial, energy and communication projects along
the Beijing-Kowloon railway line before the turn of the century.
</P>
<P>
These projects are based in seven provinces and cities along the
2,536-km-long railway line, the longest north-south artery in China.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investors are welcomed to offer direct investment in
textile, building materials, foodstuffs, tourism, power and
communication projects.
</P>
<P>
A number of cities of historical interests or scenic spots will
raise funds to build hotels, roads and other tourist facilities.
</P>
<P>
Most of the roads, bridges and power projects will be built in
the form of BOT (build-operate-transfer), local officials said.
</P>
<P>
So far, more than 170 Sino-foreign joint ventures on food and
vegetable processing, flower cultivation and fiberboard production
have become operational in cities along the road. Some of their
projects have been exported to the United States, Japan and
Southeast Asian countries.  
