<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The Portuguese ruling party,
the Socialist Party, and the biggest opposition party, the Social
Democratic Party, both took the lead in local elections held all
over the country on December 14.
</P>
<P>
The official results announced today showed that the Socialist
Party won 38.07 percent of ballots or 128 seats in local
governments. The Social Democratic party gained 32.86 percent of
votes or 127 seats.
</P>
<P>
