<DOCNO> XIE19971216.0184 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Jiang's Speech at Informal China-ASEAN </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The following is the full
text of a speech delivered on Tuesday by Chinese President Jiang
Zemin at the first Informal China-ASEAN Summit.
</P>
<P>
Entitled "Toward a Good-Neighborly Partnership of Mutual Trust
Oriented to the 21st Century," the speech reads as follows:
</P>
<P>
I feel more than happy to have the opportunity to gather
together with leaders of nine ASEAN countries for the first time
to discuss and explore the development of China-ASEAN friendship
and cooperation oriented toward the 21st century. First of all, I
wish to offer my warm congratulations to ASEAN on its 30th
anniversary.
</P>
<P>
This meeting, I believe, marks the beginning of a new stage of
development in China-ASEAN relations.
</P>
<P>
With the purpose of active participation, broadening common
ground, enhancing mutual trust and strengthening cooperation, I
have come here to explore together with ASEAN leaders the
objectives and guidelines for the development of our future
relations.
</P>
<P>
At the important historical juncture on the eve of the new
century, we should approach and handle our bilateral relations
from a long-range strategic perspective and forge a China-ASEAN
good-neighborly partnership of mutual trust oriented to the 21st
century. This is not only in conformity with the trend of the
times and in the fundamental interest of China and ASEAN
countries, but also facilitates the establishment of a just and
rational new international order and the advancement of the lofty
cause of peace and development of Asia and the world at large.
</P>
<P>
Both the Chinese and the ASEAN people are industrious and
courageous people full of wisdom. Since ancient times, they have
created brilliant civilizations and built up fine cultural
traditions full of oriental colors on their own land, thus making
important contributions to the progress of humanity. Joined
together by mountains and rivers or facing each other across the
sea, China and ASEAN countries have developed a profound
traditional friendship among the people in the course of their
age-old contacts and exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Since the modern times began, profound changes have taken place
in both China and ASEAN countries. Through a century-long struggle
and sacrifice, the Chinese people won their national liberation
and gave birth to the new China. With decades of efforts, they
have built China into a socialist country with initial
prosperity. Through protracted and arduous struggle, the people of
ASEAN countries have also shaken off the yoke of colonialism and
won their national independence and have scored commendable
achievements in their course of nation-building.
</P>
<P>
At present, both China and ASEAN countries, seizing
opportunities presented by history, have formulated development
strategies in light of their own national conditions and continued
to develop the productive forces and maintain a sustained economic
growth. China has accelerated the development of a socialist
market economy, socialist democracy and socialist culture in its
efforts to become a strong, prosperous, democratic and culturally
advanced modern country by and large by the middle of the next
century. ASEAN, on the other hand, is also pressing ahead with its
process to attain industrialization, modernization and
integration. The ASEAN Vision 2020 you have drawn up has set clear
steps and mapped out a grand blueprint in this regard. China and
ASEAN countries will continue to be dynamic throughout the world
in growth.
</P>
<P>
Both committed to the promotion of regional and global peace
and development, China and ASEAN countries are in favor of
building up their mutual trust, expanding their common ground
while reserving differences and proper handling of their
differences through friendly consultations and candid cooperation
so as to secure regional peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
The time-honored traditional friendship, similar historical
experience and common desire for peace and economic development
constitute an important basis both in history and at present for
the enhancement of the good-neighborly relations of mutual trust
and friendly cooperation between China and ASEAN countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
