opposition party in the country, announced Monday former chief
minister of Sindh province Aftab Shaaban Mirani as its candidate
for the election, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
According to the reports, Tarar comes from Punjab province and
is a close relative of PPP's Altzaz Ahsan, leader of the
opposition in the Senate.
</P>
<P>
Tarar is a former chief justice of the Lahore High Court and a
judge of the Supreme Court of Pakistan from where he retired in
1994.
</P>
<P>
He was elected to the Senate for the first time on a PML ticket
in March this year, the reports said.  
</P>
