<HEADLINE> Jiang Proposes Steps to Strengthen Partnership With ASEAN </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin Tuesday proposed four steps to build and develop a 21st
century-oriented good-neighborly partnership of mutual trust
between China and the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(ASEAN).
</P>
<P>
In a speech here at the first Informal China-ASEAN Summit,
Jiang said that China and ASEAN countries should first make the
best use of the existing mechanism of all-round dialogue and
cooperation to broaden their exchanges and cooperation in all
areas, at all levels and through all channels.
</P>
<P>
They should also give priority to promoting their economic
relations, trade and scientific and technological cooperation and
reinforcing their cooperation in resources, technology, market,
banking, information, human resources development and investment,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that they should intensify their dialogue,
co-ordination and mutual support on major regional and
international issues and in regional and international
organizations. By so doing, he said, they can jointly safeguard
the legitimate rights and interests of the developing countries
and promote their fair and equal participation in international
economic affairs.
</P>
<P>
Finally Jiang proposed that China and ASEAN countries should
continue to handle their differences or disputes through friendly
consultations and seek a progressive solution to them. If some
differences cannot be solved for the time being, he said, they
should be shelved temporarily in order to seek common ground.
</P>
<P>
He assured in the speech that China will always be "a good
neighbor, a good partner and a good friend with ASEAN countries."
</P>
</TEXT>
