<HEADLINE> South China Province Improves Management of Foreign-Funded Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, the capital of
south China's Guangdong province, is striving to improve
supervision of overseas-funded enterprises with the hopes of
stopping losses of state-owned property.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou has at least 8,400 overseas-funded enterprises, with
a total investment of 46.6 billion US dollars and 23.6 billion US
dollars in registered capital from 30 countries and regions,
including the United States, Britain, Japan, as well as Hong Kong
and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
To improve the management of these overseas-funded enterprises,
the city government has set up supervisory bodies in 32 percent of
the total of 325 foreign-funded enterprises that are under the
direct jurisdiction of the city government departments.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the city government is making a greater effort in
establishing a supervisory system in the enterprises, developing a
regulatory system, and improved management. 
</P>
</TEXT>
