<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT December 16 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- Presidents of the member countries of the
Southern Common Market (Mercosur) Monday vowed to strengthen the
process of political, economic, financial, social, cultural and
scientific integration.
</P>
<P>
The commitment was made at the 13th Summit of Mercosur closed
earlier Monday by presidents of Argentina, Paraguay, Brazil,
Uruguay, Bolivia and Chile.
</P>
<P>
In a joint communique the presidents underlined their
willingness to continue the process of setting up Mercosur
according to a model of "opened regionalism," congruent to the
norms of the World Trade Organization (WTO).
</P>
<P>
The joint communique said that three years after the
implementation of the customs unification, Mercosur was capable of
meeting challenges generated by the dynamics of integration.
</P>
<P>
TIRANA -- Italy will help Albania rebuild the naval base in
Vlore, visiting Italian Minister of Defense Beniamino Andreatta
said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Andreatta made the remark while participating in the naval
recruits' oath ceremony at Durres naval base, which marked the
restoration of the Albanian Navy fleet.
</P>
<P>
Andreatta spoke highly of the cooperation between the two
countries, especially in the military field. He said Italy was
glad to increase military aid to Albania.
</P>
<P>
Albanian Minister of Defense Sabit Brokaj thanked Italy for its
aid and support to the Albanian Army's reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
VIENNA -- The average price of the market-monitored petroleum
of the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC)
dropped to 17.23 U.S. dollars per barrel last week from 17.76
dollars a week before.
</P>
<P>
According to the organization's statistics released Monday, the
average price of OPEC has kept falling since the winter season
began this year.
</P>
<P>
KIEV -- Ukrainian Prime Minister Valery Pustovoitenko will make
a five-day official visit to China beginning December 22 to help
forge economic links with Beijing.
</P>
<P>
"Ukraine and China have expressed the wish to conduct
cooperation in many areas," said Pustovoitenko, who will lead a
delegation of about 30 officials and businessmen. "The main
objective of my visit is to find ways and means to cooperate."
</P>
<P>
He added that the two nations will sign a declaration on
enhancing trade, investment and science cooperation, an agreement
on tariff matters and a protocol on military technology
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR -- The heads of state and government from ASEAN
and China started their informal meeting here this morning.
</P>
<P>
During the summit known as Nine plus One, the first between
China and the nine ASEAN countries, the leaders will have an
extensive exchange of views on relations between China and ASEAN
so as to establish a good-neighborly partnership of mutual trust
oriented to the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin will deliver a speech at the
informal summit. 
</P>
