<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Hails China's Relations with ASEAN </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin said Tuesday that China's relations with the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) and its members have reached a new
level since the two sides established a partnership of full
dialogue.
</P>
<P>
In a speech delivered at the first Informal China-ASEAN summit
here, Jiang said, "In the past decade, China's relations with each
ASEAN country and ASEAN as an organization have made considerable
progress and reached a new level following the establishment of
China-ASEAN partnership of full dialogue."
</P>
<P>
China and ASEAN have frequently exchanged high-level visits,
steadily expanded economic relations and trade, broadened contacts
in various fields and intensified co-ordination and cooperation on
some major international and regional issues, the Chinese
president said.
</P>
<P>
He said that China has all along attached great importance to
developing its relations with ASEAN and is in favor of a positive
role by ASEAN in regional and international affairs.
</P>
<P>
"Facts have proved and will continue to prove that developing
friendly relations and cooperation between China and ASEAN is not
only in the interests of our two sides but also benefits the
Asian-Pacific region," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the two sides have agreed to establish a
good-neighborly partnership of mutual trust oriented toward the
21st century. The current summit meeting marks "the beginning of a
new stage of development in China-ASEAN relations," he added.
</P>
<P>
The time-honored traditional friendship, similar historical
experience and common desire for peace and economic development
constitute an important basis both in history and at present for
the enhancement of the good-neighborly relations of mutual trust
and friendly cooperation between China and ASEAN countries, the
Chinese president said.
</P>
<P>
He said, "Both committed to the promotion of regional and
global peace and development, China and ASEAN countries are in
favor of building up their mutual trust, expanding their common
ground while reserving differences and proper handling of their
differences through friendly consultations and candid cooperation
so as to secure regional peace and stability."
</P>
<P>
He said that at the important historical juncture on the eve of
the new century, China and ASEAN should approach and handle their
bilateral relations from a long-range strategic perspective and
forge a good-neighborly partnership of mutual trust oriented to
the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
"Looking into the 21st century, we are convinced that there
lies an even brighter future for the development, prosperity,
friendship and cooperation between China and ASEAN countries,"
Jiang said. "China will forever be a good neighbor, a good partner
and a good friend with ASEAN countries." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
