<HEADLINE> Record Export Earning for Sri Lanka's Garment Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's garment industry
has registered a record export earning of 1.58 billion U.S.
dollars in the first three quarters this year, a 30 percent
increase over the same period last year, the Daily News reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The paper said the industry made an earning of 1.22 billion
dollars from January to September in 1996.
</P>
<P>
It quoted officials in the Industrial Development Ministry as
saying that the government has decided to strengthen the garment
industry in view of its potential to earn foreign exchange.
</P>
<P>
About 50 new garment factories will be set up soon in the
country, the officials said. Each factory could employ a minimum
of 250 workers.
</P>
<P>
For those factories which are located in "the most difficult
areas," tax will be exempted for a period of eight years, the
officials said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the factories can get land at a concessionary rate.
</P>
