<HEADLINE> Italy Helps Albania Rebuild Army and Navy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Italy will help Albania rebuild
the naval base in Vlore, visiting Italian Minister of Defense
Beniamino Andreatta said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Andreatta made the remark while participating in the naval
recruits' oath ceremony at Durres naval base, which marked the
restoration of the Albanian Navy fleet.
</P>
<P>
Andreatta spoke highly of the cooperation between the two
countries, especially in the military field. He said Italy was
glad to increase military aid to Albania.
</P>
<P>
Albanian Minister of Defense Sabit Brokaj thanked Italy for its
aid and support to the Albanian Army's reconstruction. He called
on the navy to defend the country's territorial waters and the
coast.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the army, the Albanian navy was destroyed
completely during the riot at the beginning of this
year. Twenty-five vessels of the fleet sank and 33 went to Italy,
resulting in material damage of over 5.3 million US dollars (0.8
billion Lek, 150 Lek = 1 dollar).
</P>
<P>
As part of the aid from the North Atlantic Treaty Organization
(NATO), Italy has given a large amount of aid for the
reconstruction of the Albanian army. The restoration of the
Albanian navy is also part of the program. 
</P>
