<HEADLINE> Average Price of OPEC Petroleum Declines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The average price of the
market-monitored petroleum of the Organization of Petroleum
Exporting Countries (OPEC) dropped to 17.23 U.S. dollars per
barrel last week from 17.76 dollars a week before.
</P>
<P>
According to the organization's statistics released Monday, the
average price of OPEC has kept falling since the winter season
began this year.
</P>
<P>
In October this year, OPEC's average price stood at 19.54
dollars per barrel, which dropped to 18.84 dollars in November.
</P>
<P>
However, the reference price per barrel regulated inside the
organization is 21 dollars per barrel. 
