The group has increased co-operation with foreign partners like
IBM this year. IBM committed itself to selling Founder-developed
software and other products through its worldwide distribution
network, the first time for Chinese copyrighted software to enter
the global market.
</P>
<P>
The group is also optimistic about the future of Business in
Japan and the Republic of Korea, and says that sales are up 30
percent from last year.
</P>
