<HEADLINE> Ethnic Troupe Raises Performance Levels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The China Nationalities'
Central Song and Dance Ensemble is to add more realistic
characteristics to their performance on the basis of colorful
ethnic cultures, according to today's "China Daily".
</P>
<P>
This will make them more appealing to modern audiences, said
Director Li Yushan at a press conference held yesterday to mark
the 45th anniversary of the ensemble's founding.
</P>
<P>
As the only national ethnic song and dance troupe, the ensemble
was designed to preserve ethnic culture and entertain ethnic
people.
</P>
<P>
Chinese ethnic songs and dances have recently been very well
received both at home and abroad. The ensemble has been a big hit
this year, despite the lull in the performance market.
</P>
<P>
Li attributed this to the efforts of superb and wonderful
ethnic artists in the ensemble. They have developed traditional
ethnic songs and dances to a higher level.
</P>
<P>
According to Li, his ensemble will perform new songs and dances
this weekend in Beijing to mark the ensemble's 45th founding
anniversary.
</P>
<P>
In the past 45 years, the ensemble, partly financed by the
State, has performed for ethnic people on meadows, hills, and
playgrounds, and in tents in the most remote border towns.
</P>
<P>
It has developed a repertory of more than 100 programs.
</P>
