<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Honduras Approves Law Against Money Laundering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEGUCIGALPA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The Honduran Congress
today passed a bill that will curb money laundering and drug
trafficking.
</P>
<P>
The new law, which consists of 34 articles, was passed after
two heated debates.
</P>
<P>
Under the new law, military personnel and officials involved
in activities related to drug trafficking will receive a maximum
sentence of 27 years in prison.
</P>
<P>
The courts will be entitled to issue arrest or confiscation
warrants as well as taking any and all precautionary measures,
without providing notification or previous hearings.
</P>
<P>
The new law also states that anyone found guilty of money
laundering will be sentenced to 12 to 20 years in prison.
</P>
</TEXT>
