<HEADLINE> Jagge Wins World Cup Slalom at Sestriere </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Norway's former Olympic champion
Finn Christian Jagge won the men's floodlit World Cup slalom in
Sestriere on Monday night in a combined time of one minute
51.43 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Austria's Thomas Sykora was second in 1:51.77 and another
Norwegian, Hans-Petter Buraas was third in 1:51.85.
</P>
<P>
Jagge, 1992 Olympic slalom gold medalist at Albertville, had
been lying third after the first run down the Kandahar piste.
</P>
<P>
But he turned on the power in the second, despite the poor
conditions as a day-long snowfall continued throughout the
race. 
</P>
