<HEADLINE> Hubei Increases Cooperation With Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Singapore enterprises are taking
an active part in the economic construction of central China's
Hubei Province, and their investment in the province is increasing
steadily.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that by the end of October Singapore
entrepreneurs had opened 99 businesses in Hubei with more than 200
million U.S. dollars in contractual investment.
</P>
<P>
The province has used 127 million U.S. dollars of Singaporean
investment in real terms and is expected to share 40 million
U.S. dollars of trade with Singapore this year.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral trade has been greatly promoted by Singapore Prime
Minister Goh Chok Tong's visit to Hubei in 1995. And, the next
year, Goh initiated the Singapore-Hubei Trade and Investment
Committee.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Keppel Fels Company, Ltd. is now cooperating with
the province's Hong Kong-based Jingfeng Company to invite five
billion Hong Kong dollars into the local infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
The investment will mainly focus on hydropower development and
purchasing of the management rights over the Xiangfan Hanjiang
River Bridge. Singapore Power, Ltd. is planning a
200-million-U.S.-dollar power project with a company in Wuhan.
</P>
<P>
Hubei will improve the bilateral trade and investment liaison
system, provide good service for investors, and guide Singapore
enterprises to participate in local reform, said Wang Guoyao, a
provincial government official.  
</P>
