<HEADLINE> Shandong Ensures Efficient Use of World Bank Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 16 (Xinhua)-- East China's Shandong Province
has made successful efforts to ensure that World Bank loans are
used efficiently.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that the World Bank has granted loans
for 33 projects in Shandong, with the projects covering
agriculture, industry, energy, transportation, education and
public health.
</P>
<P>
To make sure that World Bank funds are efficiently used,
Shandong has set up a complete system for auditing and financial
and technical supervision.
</P>
<P>
The system has greatly helped to raise the technical level
and quality of the World Bank-funded projects.
</P>
<P>
Shandong has also invited accountants and auditors to conduct
budget auditing for the projects, a measure that has helped to cut
project costs.
</P>
<P>
