Chile will generate 290 million dollars by the year`s end.
</P>
<P>
The Association of Exporters said that Brazil is the main buyer
of Chile`S canned products, with 22 percent of the total, followed
by Japan with 13 percent and Argentina with 11 percent.
</P>
<P>
The European Union will import this year 10 percent of the
total Chilean canned food for exportation.
</P>
<P>
Supermarkets Rise Their Sales In Argentina
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Big supermarket chains increased their sales
7.9 percent over the first nine months of the year, while small
stores saw their revenues plummet.
</P>
<P>
The National Institute of Statistics and Census said that in
late years big supermarkets have become one of the most dynamic
sectors in Argentina. For in the last two years, 15 big retail
sales stores were opened, the same amount that from 1981 to 1995.
</P>
<P>
Colombia`S Economy Will Grow 3.2% In 1997
</P>
<P>
SANTA FE DE BOGOTA -- Colombia will closed the year with a
growth of 3.2 perecent in view of the swelling of exports, sales
and construction in general, reported National Planning Director
Cecilia Lopez Montano.
</P>
<P>
The official asserted that growth can be seen in all sectors of
the economy, while over the last quarter of the year, the gross
domestic product rose by 6 percent.
</P>
