<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Air France to Sell One Third of Stocks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 15 (Xinhua) -- France's national carrier Air
France will sell one third of its stocks to its employees and
investors in stock markets in an unprecedented privatization
project which is expected to begin in June 1998.
</P>
<P>
Air France president Jean-Cyril Spinetta told the press today
that his company will sell 20-25 percent of the stocks in stock
market to obtain "a stable quotation" and ensure the value of the
stocks to be owned by its employees.
</P>
<P>
The employees can also choose to subscribe to the stocks when
they are sold in the market, he said.
</P>
<P>
The company will have to obtain the green light from the
Ministry of Economy before it can sell its stocks to the market,
and the exact amount of the stocks to be sold by the company is
unknown yet.
</P>
<P>
An earlier refusal by the Socialist government to privatize the
company resulted in the resignation of its former president
Christian Blanc three months ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
