<HEADLINE> MIF Approves Assistance for Environmental Fund In Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The Multilateral Investment
Fund (MIF) today announced the approval of a 4 million U.S. dollar
investment in a risk capital fund that will support small
companies in Mexico whose activities improve the environment.
</P>
<P>
The North American Environmental Fund will provide capital to
firms engaged in such activities as recycling of wastes, cleanup
of air and water pollution, and production of commercial products
such as industrial purifiers, solar energy systems, and products
that are biodegradable.
</P>
<P>
The Overseas Economic Cooperation Fund of Japan and the
National Financiera of Mexico each contribute 2 million
dollars in cofinancing for the project.
</P>
<P>
The MIF, an autonomous fund administered by the Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB), provides grants and investments to promote
private sector growth, labor force training and small enterprise
development in Latin America and the Caribbean. 
</P>
