<HEADLINE> France, UAE to Sign Warplane Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, December 15 (Xinhua) -- France and the UAE are
expected to sign a billion-dollar-worth warplane deal during
French President Jacques Chirac's two-day visit which began here
today, an informed source said.
</P>
<P>
The source, close to the French Embassy here, said the UAE has
agreed earlier this month to buy from France 35 Mirage 9-2000s, a
new generation of the Mirage 5-2000s, and the two countries will
clinch the deal during Chirac's visit.
</P>
<P>
The warplane deal is worth some 3 billion U.S. dollars and it
is part of a UAE 80-fighter package, said the source.
</P>
<P>
In the past years, the UAE has bought from Paris more than 50
combat planes, most of them are Mirage 2000s, in a bid to beef up
its air force.
</P>
<P>
The tiny Gulf country also signed with France a defense
agreement in 1995 to boost their military cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
