Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe on economic, political and
bilateral issues, as well as the current situation in the whole
southern African region and the Great Lakes region.
</P>
<P>
Albright's seven-nation tour which is aimed to advance U.S.
interests in Africa included Ethiopia, Uganda, Rwanda, the
Democratic Republic of Congo, Angola and South Africa. Zimbabwe
is the last leg. 
