<HEADLINE> New Banana Variety Found in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- A new variety of banana which
are drought and disease resistant has been found by Ugandan
researchers, The New Vision reported today.
</P>
<P>
Wilberforce Tushemereirwe, head of the banana program at
Kawanda Agricultural Research Institute in central Uganda, said
the variety, FHIA01, produces bigger bunches than the traditional
ones.
</P>
<P>
The banana variety has been tested in various places in the
country and can be cooked, eaten as ripe banana and made into
juice, researchers from the institute said.
</P>
<P>
The researchers planned to establish plots in 20 of the 45
districts in the country to multiply the new variety and to
provide local farmers with the planting material. 
</P>
