<HEADLINE> UNICEF on African Babies Malnourishment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Of the total number of
babies born annually in the African continent, one of every three
is udnerweight due to malnourishment, the United Nations
Children's Fund (UNICEF) said here today.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the UNICEF here said a substantial
number of African infants born annually weigh below normal due to
abject shortage of balanced diet.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that millions of children in various parts
of the world face similar problems due to suppressions on their
mothers.
</P>
<P>
Of the 12 million infants udner five who die annually due to
curable diseases in the developing world, the cases of 6 million
are related directly or indirectly to malnourishment, the
statement added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
