<HEADLINE> Representatives of Greece, Former Yugoslav Republic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Representatives of
Greece and the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia met on
December 9 and 12 at the Headquarters of the United Nations under the
auspices of the Personal Envoy of the Secretary-General, Cyrus
Vance, a statement issued by the spokesman's office said today.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the meeting was aimed to exchange views in
the context of Article 5 of the Interim Accord signed on
September, 13, 1995, by the two sides.
</P>
<P>
The Greek side was reprepresented by its permanent
Representative to the United Nations, Ambassador
Christos Zacharakis, and the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia
was represented by Ambassador Ivan Tosevski, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
The statement also said the two sides had agreed to meet again
in late January 1998.  
</P>
