<HEADLINE> Lesotho Bank Makes Top Management Reshuffle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of Lesotho
fired its top management today and replaced them with a team of
consultants who will run the financial institution for the next
six months, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
In a statement broadcast over the state-controlled Radio
Lesotho, Finance Minister Lkete Ketso said the Lesotho
government, as sole shareholder of the bank, had decided to
embark on "the re-vitalization and re-orientation program with a
view to strengthening the bank's capacity".
</P>
<P>
Ketso said that upgrading of performance will be undertaken
by a highly experienced team of experts commissioned by the
government in partnership with the World Bank.
</P>
<P>
The Lesotho Bank operated normally after the mass dismissal,
the sources said. 
</P>
