<HEADLINE> Tajik Aircraft Crashes in UAE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, December 15 (Xinhua) -- A Tajik civil plane crashed
in the United Arab Emirates (UAE) tonight, killing more than 80
people, informed sources said.
</P>
<P>
The plane, with 77 passengers and 9 crew members on board,
crashed in the desert about 13 kilometers from Sharjah, a UAE city
some 200 kilometers from the capital Abu Dhabi, the UAE's Wam news
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
An informed source from the Sharjah airport told Xinhua on
telephone that the plane crashed at 19:30 local time (1530 GMT).
</P>
<P>
More than 80 people were killed and another two were seriously
injured, the source said, on condition of anonymity.
</P>
<P>
The flight number of the plane, known as Tabolov 154, is not
yet available. The cause of the crack remains unknown.
</P>
<P>
Emergency teams from Sharjah and Dubai, another UAE city near
Sharjah have rushed to the spot, witnesses said.


