<HEADLINE> Over 600 Nigerian Policemen Arrested for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, December 15 (Xinhua) -- About 650 policemen and 52
customs men across Nigeria have been arrested for corrupt practices
since a crack squad was set up in February 1994 by the
inspector-general of police.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, more than 206,000 naira (about 2,600 U.S. Dollars) has
been seized extorted from people, the News Agency of Nigeria reported
today, quoting police sources.
</P>
<P>
Also apprehended are 46 vehicle inspection officers, 26 road safety
inspection marshals, 29 immigration officers and 19 local government
staff, with their extorted money.
</P>
<P>
Last month, the police announced the dismissal of 350 men and
officers for various offenses ranging from extortion to flagrant abuse
of office.
</P>
<P>
However, the situation of corrupted practices among officers in
uniform is still grave in the country, partly due to the poor quality
and pay of the police force.
</P>
<P>
To make things better, the police announced earlier this month the
setting up of in-house anti-corruption squads in its renewed bid to
identify and cleanse the force of bad eggs.
</P>
<P>
According to the police, corrupt officers will be dismissed if
0h_irmed. 
</P>
