<HEADLINE> Turkey, Russia Sign Cooperation Accords </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Turkey and Russia signed here
today several agreements on cooperation in the fields of trade,
economy and science following three-hour-long official talks
between the Turkish and Russian prime ministers.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Prime Minister Mesut Yilmaz and his visiting Russian
counterpart Victor Chernomyrdin, who arrived here today for a
two-day official visit to Turkey, signed a cooperation program,
agreements on prevention of double taxation, mutual encouragement
and protection of investment, energy cooperation, cooperation on
natural gas and juridical assistance, and a memorandum on high
technology.
</P>
<P>
The Russian prime minister's visit was aimed at enhancing
bilateral ties, including realizing multi-billion gas deal plans
and seeking a solution to the disputed straits.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day visit, Chernomyrdin has been expected to
submit Russia's request for Turkey to make some changes to the
rules in respects of traffic in the Turkish straits, the Bosphorus
and the Dardanelles.
</P>
<P>
They will also discuss some important issues, including the
controversial 150 kilometer-range S-300 missiles, which are
planned to be sold to Cyprus by Moscow. 
</P>
</TEXT>
