<HEADLINE> 12 Killed in Land Mine Explosion in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Twelve people were killed and
eight others injured today when a minibus hit a land mine in
southeastern Turkey, local private TV Star reported.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the minibus was shuttling between two
villages in Mardin town in the region when it hit a land mine
early this morning reportedly planted by the rebels of the
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK).
</P>
<P>
Among the people who died in the explosion were women and
children, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Turkish security forces launched a large-scale
operation against the PKK late Sunday in and near Mountain Cudi,
close to Sirnak province linking northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The operation began after a tip-off that a group of PKK
militants had infiltrated into Mountain Cudi from northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish government troops have been carrying out a
cross-border operation in the area for nearly a week.
</P>
<P>
Turkish fighter planes heavily bombarded Mountain Cudi and
nearby areas late Sunday while the Turkish security forces began
a ground operation early Monday with the aim of blocking all
escape routes the PKK rebels from Turkey into northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a 13-year-old separatist war for
autonomy in eastern and southeastern Turkey, which has claimed
over 28,000 lives since August 1984. 
</P>
</TEXT>
