<HEADLINE> Angola Ministers Council Passes '98 Budget </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Meeting of the Angolan
Ministers council has passed the budget for 1998, which puts
priority on creating economic condition for national
reconciliation.
</P>
<P>
A communique issued at the end of the meeting said that the
budget will aim at the stabilization of the nation's currency and
financial situation through raising the non-oil income,
controlling budget deficit and limiting institutional purchase.
</P>
<P>
The meeting whih opened last Friday and ended today also
passed an economic stabilization and revitalization plan for the
period between 1998 and 2000.
</P>
<P>
The communique said that the goal in the coming three years is
to consolidate the national reconciliation, guarantee national defense
security, realize political, economic and financial stability
and raise the economic position of southern Angola.
</P>
<P>
The budget is to be handed over to the parliament for approval.
</P>
